<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="41.[189,310,1055,1081]" box="[189,310,1055,1081]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1055,1081]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1055,1081]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[187,1399,1101,1198]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit, 2021" authorityName="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit" authorityYear="2021" box="[301,478,1101,1128]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Tafana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chimire" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[301,478,1101,1128]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Tafana chimire</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[485,576,1102,1128]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble other males of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MNHN" baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[918,1009,1101,1127]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Tafana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silhavyi">
<emphasis box="[918,1009,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">silhavyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the laminar base of the apophysis of the embolus, but differ from them by the base of the retrolateral tibial apophysis with a hook shape apically and the presence of a large basal prominent protuberance on the tegulum (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1371,1172,1198]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="42.[189,232,1731,1757]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,834,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-210@42.[189,1398,834,1690]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Fig. 24. Tafana chimire sp. nov. (MACN-Ar), ♂. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, ventral view (arrow indicating character). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ABE =apophysis of base of the embolus; bTP=basal tegular protuberance; Ch =character; E=embolus; PA=patellar apophysis; RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis; T=tegulum. Scale bars: A–B =2.16 mm; C–E= 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4655479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4655479/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 24C–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
